  PreLevelDialogue:
  - "Kid, the TIME HAS COME! That\u2019s right, your father has entrusted BILL to
    give his sword to YOU! The family sword I\u2019ve heard, nothing but the best
    damascus steel or something."
  - "Okay I\u2019ll admit I don\u2019t really know anything about swords, it\u2019s
    the thought that counts though no? Either way there is more important business,
    which is BUSINESS! We, yes WE are going to make so much money from this."
  - "What will Bill do? GAH You\u2019re already undervaluing me? Not only am I going
    to teach you the ropes of sculpting, I\u2019m going to be the one who brings
    in all the opportunities."
  - "Opportunities for MONEY. Your family business was missing a trick, we are going
    to make the BEST sculptures for the richest people we know, and then when their
    posh friends see OUR sculptures, they\u2019ll want to get in on it."
  - "Exponential growth, the first rule of business school! But first, we need to
    teach you the ropes, you can\u2019t even hold your sword let alone make a sculpture."
  - "Don\u2019t worry we\u2019ll start simple, I\u2019ve got you some marble already
    - don\u2019t worry Bill\u2019s gotchu. We\u2019ll start with some pretty shapes.
    Go on chop chop! Bill\u2019s waiting."
